===Absolute monarchies===
Specifically, monarchies in which the monarch's exercise of power is unconstrained by any substantive constitutional law.

{{colbegin}}
*{{flag|Brunei}}
*{{flag|Eswatini}}
*{{flag|Oman}}
*{{flag|Qatar}}
*{{flag|Saudi Arabia}}
*{{flag|United Arab Emirates}}<ref>The UAE's constitution establishes the state as a federation of emirates, with the federal president drawn from hereditary emirs, but each emirate in turn functions as an absolute monarchy</ref>
*{{flag|Vatican City}}<ref name="Va">The Vatican is an [[elective monarchy|elective]] absolute monarchy and a Roman Catholic theocracy; its monarch, the [[Pope]], is the head of the global [[Roman Catholic Church]]. His power within the Vatican City State is unlimited by any constitution, but all persons resident within the Vatican have consented to obey the Pope, either by virtue of being ordained Catholic clergy or members of the [[Swiss Guard]].</ref>
{{colend}}

'''''Note: Vatican City may be considered a theocracy as the monarch is elected by a religious body<ref name="Va"/>'''''

===One-party states===
States in which political power is ''by law'' concentrated within [[one-party state|one political party]] whose operations are largely fused with the government hierarchy (as opposed to states where the law establishes a [[multi-party system]] but [[Dominant-party system|this fusion is not achieved anyway through electoral fraud or simple inertia]]). However, some do have elected governments.

{{colbegin}}
*{{flag|China|name=China, People's Republic of}} <small>([[Communist Party of China|Communist Party]] leads the [[United Front (People's Republic of China)|United Front]]) ([[List of political parties in the People's Republic of China|list]])</small>
*{{flag|Cuba}} <small>([[Communist Party of Cuba|Communist Party]]) ([[List of political parties in Cuba|list]])</small>
*{{flag|Eritrea}} <small>([[People's Front for Democracy and Justice]]) ([[List of political parties in Eritrea|list]])</small>
*{{flag|Korea, North}} <small>([[Workers' Party of Korea|Workers' Party]] leads the [[Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland|Democratic Front]]) ([[Politics of North Korea|list]])</small>
*{{flag|Laos}} <small>([[Lao People's Revolutionary Party|People's Revolutionary Party]] leads the [[Lao Front for National Construction|Front for National Construction]]) ([[List of political parties in Laos|list]])</small>
*''{{flag|Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic}}'' <small>([[Polisario Front]]) ([[Politics of the Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic]])</small>
*{{flag|Vietnam}} <small>([[Communist Party of Vietnam|Communist Party]] leads the [[Vietnamese Fatherland Front|Fatherland Front]]) ([[List of Vietnamese political parties|list]])</small>
{{colend}}

===Military dictatorships===
The nation's military control the organs of government and all high-ranking political executives are also members of the military hierarchy.

