==Systems of internal structure==

===Unitary states===
{{Main article|Unitary state}}A [[State (polity)|state]] governed as a single power in which the [[central government]] is ultimately supreme and any [[Administrative division|administrative divisions]] (sub-national units) exercise only the powers that the central government chooses to delegate. 
The majority of states in the world have a unitary system of government. Of the 193 [[Member states of the United Nations|UN member states]], 165 are governed as unitary states.

==== Centralised unitary states: ====

====Regionalised unitary states:====
{{Main article|Regional state}}
States in which the [[central government]] has delegated some of its powers to regional authorities.

{{colbegin}}
*{{flag|Bolivia}} <small>(9 [[Administrative divisions of Bolivia|regions]], of which 9 are autonomous)</small>
*{{flag|China, People's Republic of}} <small>(22 [[Provinces of China|provinces]], 5 [[Autonomous regions of China|autonomous regions]], 4 [[Direct-controlled municipality of China|province-level municipalities]],  2 [[Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China|special administrative regions]], and 1 [[Taiwan Province, People's Republic of China|claimed province]])</small>
*{{flag|China, Republic of}} <small>(2 [[Provinces of Taiwan|provinces]], 6 [[Special municipality (Taiwan)|special municipalities]], 33 [[provinces of China|claimed provinces]], 3 [[Special administrative regions of China#ROC special administrative regions|claimed special administrative regions]], 2 regions, 12 [[special municipality (Republic of China)|claimed special municipalities]], 14 leagues, and 4 special banners)</small>
*{{flag|France}} <small>(18 [[regions of France|regions]], of which 6 are autonomous)</small>
*{{flag|Indonesia}} <small>(34 [[provinces of Indonesia|provinces]], of which 5 provinces have special status)</small>
*{{flag|Italy}} <small>(20 [[regions of Italy|regions]], of which 5 are autonomous)</small>
*{{flag|Kingdom of the Netherlands}} <small>(4 [[Countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands|constituent countries]])</small> 
*{{flag|Philippines}} <small>([[Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao|one autonomous region]] subdivided into 5 [[Provinces of the Philippines|provinces]] and 113 [[List of primary local government units of the Philippines|other provinces and independent cities]] grouped into [[Regions of the Philippines|17 other non-autonomous regions]])</small>
*{{flag|Portugal}} <small>(2 [[autonomous regions of Portugal|autonomous regions]])</small>
*{{flag|Spain}} <small>(17 [[Autonomous communities of Spain|autonomous communities]], [[Communities of chartered regime|15 communities of common-regime, 1 community of chartered regime, 3 chartered provinces]], 2 [[autonomous cities of Spain|autonomous cities]])</small>
*{{flag|Tanzania}} <small>(21 mainland regions and {{flag|Zanzibar}})</small>
*{{flag|Ukraine}} <small>(24 [[Oblasts of Ukraine|oblasts]], 2 [[City with special status|cities with special status]], and {{flag|Crimea}})</small>
*{{flag|United Kingdom}} <small>(4 [[Countries of the United Kingdom|constituent countries]], 3 [[Devolution in the United Kingdom|devolved administrations]])</small>
