===Federation===
{{Main article|Federation}}
States in which the [[federal government]] shares power with semi-independent regional governments. The central government may or may not be (in theory) a creation of the regional governments.

{{colbegin}}
*{{flag|Argentina}} <small>([[Provinces of Argentina|23 provinces]] and one autonomous city: [[Buenos Aires]])</small>
*{{flag|Australia}} <small>([[States and territories of Australia|six states and three territories]])</small>
*{{flag|Austria}} <small>([[States of Austria|nine states]])</small>
*{{flag|Belgium}} <small>([[Communities, regions and language areas of Belgium|three regions and three linguistic communities]])</small>
*{{flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}} <small>([[Political divisions of Bosnia and Herzegovina|two entities]] and [[Brčko District|one district]])</small>
*{{flag|Brazil}} <small>([[States of Brazil|26 states]] and the [[Federal District (Brazil)|Federal District]])</small>
*{{flag|Canada}} <small>([[Provinces and territories of Canada|ten provinces and three territories]])</small>
*{{flag|Comoros}} <small>([[Anjouan]], [[Grande Comore]], [[Mohéli]])</small>
*{{flag|Ethiopia}} <small>([[Regions of Ethiopia|nine regions and two chartered cities]])</small>
*{{flag|Germany}} <small>([[States of Germany|16 states]])</small>
*{{flag|India}} <small>([[States and territories of India|29 states and seven union territories]])</small>
*{{flag|Iraq}} <small>([[Governorates of Iraq|18 governorates]] and [[Regions of Iraq|one region]]: [[Iraqi Kurdistan|Kurdistan]])</small>
*{{flag|Malaysia}} <small>([[States of Malaysia|13 states]] and [[Federal Territory (Malaysia)|three federal territories]])</small>
*{{flag|Mexico}} <small>([[States of Mexico|31 states]] and one federal district: [[Mexico City]])</small>
*{{flag|Federated States of Micronesia}} <small>([[Chuuk State|Chuuk]], [[Kosrae]], [[Pohnpei]] and [[Yap]])</small>
*{{flag|Nepal}} <small>([[Nepalese Federal States|seven provinces]])</small>
*{{flag|Nigeria}} <small>([[States of Nigeria|36 states]] and one federal territory: [[Federal Capital Territory (Nigeria)|Federal Capital Territory]])</small>
*{{flag|Pakistan}} <small>([[Provinces and territories of Pakistan|4 provinces, 2 autonomous areas and 2 territories]])</small>
*{{flag|Russia}} <small>([[Oblasts of Russia|46 oblasts]], [[Republics of Russia|22 republics]], [[Krais of Russia|nine krais]], [[Autonomous okrugs of Russia|four autonomous okrugs]], [[Federal cities of Russia|three federal cities]], [[Jewish Autonomous Oblast|one autonomous oblast]])</small>
*{{flag|Saint Kitts and Nevis}} <small>([[Saint Kitts]], [[Nevis]])</small>
*{{flag|South Sudan}} <small>([[Subdivisions of South Sudan|ten states]])</small>
*{{flag|Sudan}} <small>([[States of Sudan|17 states]])</small>
*{{flag|Switzerland}} <small>([[Cantons of Switzerland|26 cantons]])</small>
*{{flag|United Arab Emirates}} <small>([[Emirates of the United Arab Emirates|seven emirates]])</small>
*{{flag|United States}} <small>([[U.S. state|50 states]], one [[incorporated territory]], and one federal district: [[District of Columbia]])</small>
*{{flag|Venezuela}} <small>([[States of Venezuela|23 states]], [[Venezuelan Capital District|one capital district]] and [[Federal dependencies of Venezuela|one federal dependency]])</small>
{{colend}}

===Confederation===
{{Main article|Confederation}}A union of sovereign states, united for purposes of common action often in relation to other states. Usually created by a [[treaty]], confederations of states tend to be established for dealing with critical issues, such as defense, foreign relations, internal trade or currency, with the [[Central government|general government]] being required to provide support for all its members.{{colbegin}}
*{{flag|Switzerland}}<ref name="Assembly-independent" /><ref name="CH" />
{{colend}}

==European Union==
{{main article|List of European Union member states by political system}}

The exact political character of the [[European Union]] is debated, some arguing that it is ''[[sui generis]]'' (unique), but others arguing that it has features of a [[federation]] or a [[confederation]]. It has elements of [[intergovernmentalism]], with the [[European Council]] acting as its collective "president", and also elements of [[supranationalism]], with the [[European Commission]] acting as its executive and bureaucracy.<ref>For more detailed discussion, see John McCormick, ''European Union Politics'' (Palgrave Macmillan, 2011), Chapters 1 and 2.</ref> But it is not easily placed in any of the above categories.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}

