{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2011}} The '''Philosophy of Time Society''' is an organization which grew out of a [[National Endowment for the Humanities]] Summer Seminar on the [[Philosophy of space and time|Philosophy of Time]] offered by [[George N. Schlesinger]] in 1991.<ref name="nottingham1">{{cite web|url=http://www.nottingham.ac.uk/philtimesoc/intro.aspx |title=Welcome to the Philosophy of Time Society – The University of Nottingham |publisher=Nottingham.ac.uk |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref> The organization itself was formed in 1993.<ref name="nottingham1"/> Its stated goal is "to promote the study of the philosophy of time from a broad [[Analytic philosophy|analytic perspective]], and to provide a forum as an affiliated group with the [[American Philosophical Association]], to discuss the issues in and related to the philosophy of time."<ref name="nottingham1"/>
The Philosophy of Time Society's meetings are held at the meetings of the [[American Philosophical Association]]. In the past, they have included many notable scholars such as Hud Hudson,<ref>http://myweb.facstaff.wwu.edu/aristos/CV</ref> [[Robin Le Poidevin]],<ref name="springer1">{{cite web|url=https://www.springer.com/philosophy/book/978-1-4020-0062-1 |title=The Importance of Time |publisher=Springer.com |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref> Ned Markosian,<ref name="springer1"/> [[Hugh Mellor]],<ref name="springer1"/> [[John Perry (philosopher)|John Perry]],<ref name="springer1"/> [[Theodore Sider]],<ref name="nottingham2">{{cite web |url=http://www.nottingham.ac.uk/PhilTimeSoc/conferences.aspx |title=Conferences – The University of Nottingham |publisher=Nottingham.ac.uk |accessdate=November 10, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805093633/http://www.nottingham.ac.uk/PhilTimeSoc/conferences.aspx |archivedate=August 5, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Michael Tooley]],<ref name="springer1"/> [[Dean Zimmerman]].<ref name="nottingham2"/> Topics of papers have varied widely.<ref name="springer1"/>
