In [[information theory]], '''specific-information''' is the [[Placeholder name|generic name]] given to the family of state-dependent measures that in expectation converge to the [[mutual information]]. There are currently three known varieties of specific information usually denoted <math>I_V</math>, <math>I_S</math>, and <math>I_{ssi}</math>.
The specific-information between a [[random variable]] <math>X</math> and a state <math>Y=y</math> is written as :<math>I( X ; Y = y)</math>.

